title: A once restrained Fauci unleashes on White House days before election
description: • White House responds to Fauci's criticism

title: Quebec stabbing: Two dead after attack by man in medieval clothes
description: A male suspect is in custody after two people were killed and five others injured in a stabbing attack Saturday night in Quebec City, reported CNN partner CBC News.

title: Thai King addresses protesters in rare public comments, saying he 'loves them all the same'
description: As mass anti-government protests build across Thailand and calls for reform of the monarchy grow, King Maha Vajiralongkorn has called his country "the land of compromise," suggesting there may be a way out of the months-long political impasse.

title: CNN Washington Bureau Chief explains the states to watch on election night
description: CNN Washington Bureau Chief Sam Feist tells Brian Stelter which states will be important to watch on election night.

title: GOP Sen. says 'we haven't beaten' Covid-19 as Trump pushes false claims on pandemic
description: Republican Sen. Rick Scott said Sunday that the US has not beaten the coronavirus pandemic as President Donald Trump is falsely claiming that the country is "rounding the corner" on the surging  virus in the final days of the 2020 campaign.

title: If correct, Trump is in a far better position than assumed, and we could be in for a much closer race
description: Poll of the week: A new Des Moines Register/Selzer and Co. poll from Iowa likely voters has President Donald Trump leading Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden by a 48% to 41% margin.

title: Cristiano Ronaldo scores a brace on his return to action after contracting Covid-19
description: It's safe to say that Cristiano Ronaldo has missed football.

title: America again has a choice between the past and the future
Obama nails three-pointer while campaigning
description: Barack Obama called game.

title: Boris Johnson accused of 'giving in to scientific advisers' as England heads for lockdown
description: Boris Johnson was accused of "giving in to scientific advisers" by a former leader of his Conservative Party after the UK Prime Minister announced a lockdown for England following weeks of warnings from the experts.

title: Death toll from Aegean Sea quake rises to 60
description: The powerful earthquake that hit the Aegean Sea on Friday has killed 58 people in Turkey, the country's disaster agency said Sunday. Two people also died on the Greek island of Samos, Greek authorities said.

title: Day of the Dead has everything to do with the afterlife, love and those colorful skulls you've seen around
description: Families are spreading bulks of marigold petals, lighting up candles for their loved ones and some are even wearing colorful skull makeup.

title: Strongest typhoon of 2020 slams the Philippines, killing at least 10
description: A super typhoon has barreled into the southern part of the Philippines' main island of Luzon on Sunday, bringing "catastrophic" violent winds and intense rain with two landfalls so far, the country's weather bureau said.

title: Portland Police declare a riot
description: Police in Portland, Oregon, declared a riot Saturday night after officers observed protesters damaging multiple businesses, the Portland Police Bureau said in a news release.

title: Investigators consider 'personal dispute' in shooting of priest with sawed-off shotgun
description: Investigators are "leaning towards" treating Saturday's attack on a Greek Orthodox priest in Lyon, France, as a "personal dispute," according to a source close to the investigation.

title: Pre-Election Day vote surpasses two-thirds of all 2016 ballots cast
description: With just three days until Election Day, pre-election voting has now surpassed two-thirds of all ballots cast during the 2016 presidential election.

title: Mercedes seals record Constructors' title after Lewis Hamilton wins the Emilia Romagna GP
description: Mercedes has won the Constructors' Championship for a record seventh consecutive time after yet more success at the Emilia Romagna GP on Sunday.

title: 'SNL' has Jim Carrey's Joe Biden read a spooky Halloween story about the election
description: In its latest episode, which took place on Halloween, "Saturday Night Live" had Jim Carrey's Joe Biden read a scary story about something that is spooking a lot of Americans: next week's election.

title: Police use pepper spray to break up North Carolina march to polling place
description: Law enforcement officers used pepper spray on Saturday to break up a march to a polling place in Graham, North Carolina.

title: Analysis: US again has a choice between the past and the future
description: This week, America decides whether the past can hold off the future one more time.

title: In Europe and the US, abortion rights are under renewed threat
description: The Abortion Dream Team usually receives about 400 calls a month, from women seeking advice and information. Last week, the Polish advocacy group had 700 in the space of three days, according to team member Justyna Wydrzynska.

title: Watch: 'SNL' features a scary tale for Biden
description: Jim Carrey's Joe Biden read a scary story about something that is spooking a lot of Americans: next week's election.

title: What is Movember or NoShavember anyway?
description: It's the first of November, which means it's the start of Movember or NoShavember. You've likely seen these words before and may have wondered what they're all about.

title: A once restrained Fauci unleashes on White House days before election
Australia records zero local coronavirus cases for first time since June
description: Australia registered no new local Covid-19 cases on Saturday for the first time since June 9, marking a major milestone in the country's battle against the deadly virus.

title: America's role as global leader all but died under Trump. The world was outgrowing it anyway
description: The United States was never expected to last this long as the world's leader. For more than seven decades, America has buttressed the "rules-based order," acting as the world's police and its moral champion, whether its allies and enemies liked it or not. That's no longer the case.

title: The 'dose' of coronavirus a person gets may determine how sick they get; masks could help
description: "The dose makes the poison" is an adage credited to Paracelsus, a Swiss physician-philosopher from the early Renaissance.

title: Joe Biden discloses names of elite fundraisers
description: More than 800 individuals and couples each raised at least $100,000 to help fund former Vice President Joe Biden's presidential bid, according to a list of fundraisers the Democrat's campaign released Saturday night, just days before the election.

title: Grandma Wong was a key figure in Hong Kong's protest movement -- until she disappeared
description: With her gray hair and huge British flag, 64-year-old Alexandra Wong was a striking figure on the frontlines of last year's pro-democracy protests -- until she disappeared.

title: Connery was the ultimate movie star
Biden cancels Texas event after Trump supporters surround bus
description: President Donald Trump on Saturday night appeared to embrace the actions of supporters in Texas who surrounded a Joe Biden campaign bus in what a Biden campaign official described as an attempt to slow down the bus and run it off the road.

title: Shanghai could be the world's biggest IPO market this year. Holding the title will be tough
description: Shanghai is on track to steal the global IPO crown this year, bolstering a drive by Beijing to reduce its reliance on foreign financial markets and giving China a powerful one-two fundraising punch with regional powerhouse Hong Kong.
